1. **Section B Collections** — 7 missing collections (LinkedList, HashSet, TreeSet, TreeMap, Queue, PriorityQueue, Deque) that are only in the comparison report but not actively used in business logic (~35 marks)
2. **Section E Reports** — 6 stub reports that need real implementations (~15 marks)
3. **Section E UML diagrams** — class/ER/layer diagrams (~10 marks within Section E)
4. **Section F Rule 5** — Emergency patient PriorityQueue needs real code implementation (~5 marks)

### Important:
5. **Section D** — Verify @Transactional, pagination, sorting, filtering, cascade types are fully operational
6. **Section A** — Add copy constructors to remaining entities (Patient, Doctor, Nurse, Appointment, etc.)
7. **Section D** — Write Singleton pattern explanation docs

### Low priority / already documented:
8. **Section A Req 6** — Verify displayProfile / calculateCharges / generateReport exist in all relevant entities
